main event: Radar tracks of unidentified aircraft were detected over Sakhalin, Japan between February 21-22, 1951.
interesting points: Tracks were observed using ground radar, with speeds ranging from 150 to 300 mph., A total of 10 tracks of unidentified aircraft were identified during the observation period., The tracks were tentatively evaluated as U.S. aircraft by Air Defense Controllers., Various types of observations were noted including ground-visual tracking., The observation noted varying speeds and unidentified aircraft activity during hours of darkness.
